[normal] Furthermore, the Tribunal endorsed a 
[normal]'
[normal]green
[normal]-
[normal]light
[normal]'
[normal] regulatory approach:
[normal] 
[normal]'
[normal]If there had remained any legitimate regulatory concerns following a proper examination of the evidence originally provided to it, the Tribunal concludes that it would have been appropriate for the Respondent to work with the charity to improve its processes before considering exercising its regulatory powers.
[normal]'
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]A[bold]ssessment of responses[bold]19
[normal]              
[normal]T
[normal]his 
[normal]track 
[normal]record 
[normal]of the 
[normal]Charity 
[normal]Commission
[normal] does not match the seriousness with which the threat of terrorism is 
[normal]depicted
[normal] in CONTEST. 
[normal]That verdict is subject to two p
[normal]rovisos
[normal]. One is that 
[normal]further 
[normal]efforts have been 
[normal]instituted
[normal] since 2006 to 
[normal]improve the relevant guidance
[normal].
[normal] The second point is that there are competing public interests which may legitimately affect the degree and manner of intervention by regulators.
[normal] These 
[normal]two 
[normal]p
[normal]rovisos
[normal] will 
[normal]now 
[normal]be considered.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]20
[normal]              
[normal]In response to the 
[normal]evident 
[normal]perils of terrorist abuse and infiltration of charities, 
[normal]the Home Office and HM Treasury 
[normal]reviewed the 
[normal]policing
[normal] regime
[normal] i
[normal]n their 
[normal]2007 
[normal]report, 
[normal]Review of Safeguards to Protect the Charitable Sector (England and Wales) from Terrorist Abuse
[normal]’.
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]he
[normal] government departments
[normal] urge
[normal]d
[normal] the Charity Commission to reinforce 
[normal]its guidance
[normal], and it 
[normal]responded 
[normal]in 2008 
[normal]by 
[normal]publish
[normal]ing
[normal] 
[normal]its
[normal] 
[normal]Counter-Terrorism Strategy
[normal] wherein it promised
[normal] 'zero tolerance'.
[normal] In pursuance of 
[normal]its
[normal] strategy, various actions have been undertaken to improve trustee awareness, 
[normal]including 
[normal]oversight through a Proactive Monitoring Unit, cooperation between enforcement agencies, and 
[normal]greater 
[normal]intervention. 
[normal]Published advice has been 
[normal]further 
[normal]elaborated through the issuance of an 
[normal]Operational Guidance
[normal] 
[normal]and a 
[normal]Compliance Toolkit
[normal], setting out the Commission’s approach, and underlining the duties of vigilance and disclosure of trustees, illustrating the possible threats, 
[normal]and giving advice about the work of the Counter Terrorism Team which forms part of the Intensive Casework Unit in Compliance and Support.
[normal] 
